The '''Northern Colorado Writers Workshop''' is an invitation-only, non-profit writing workshop founded in 1972 by [[Edward Bryant]]. The writing genres of its members include mainly [[science fiction]], [[fantasy]], [[horror fiction|horror]], and [[mystery fiction|mystery]].<ref>[https://essaychip.com Professional Writers Workshop]</ref> Membership in the workshop is generally limited to professional and near-professional writers, and includes a number of [[Hugo award|Hugo]], [[Nebula award|Nebula]], [[Bram Stoker Award|Bram Stoker]], [[International Horror Guild Award|International Horror Guild]], and [[World Fantasy Award]] winners.
